				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Tales of the Borrowers" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>A card game based on the Borrowers, the tiny people that live hidden in our houses and borrow only what they need.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players share a common deck comprising 10 cards of each of 7 card types: Places, Threats, Escapes, Friends, Foods, Objects, and Tools. Players start with a hand of 7 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns with each turn comprising 3 phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.   Draw Phase&amp;#10;-    Draw Cards from the deck to fill your hand to 7 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2.   Action Phase&amp;#10;-    You may discard 1 card for its effect: &amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Places = Discard 1 more card and draw 2 cards&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Threats = Opponent discards 1 random card from hand &amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Escapes = Steal 1 random card from an opponent&amp;rsquo;s hand&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Friends = Give this card to opponent and draw 2 cards&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Foods = Draw 1 card&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Objects = Put any card from the discard into your hand&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Tools = Discard hand and draw 7 new cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3.   Meld Phase&amp;#10;-    You may make a meld of 7 cards of one of the following 10 types:&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Borrower&amp;rsquo;s Feast: 3 Friends + 4 Foods&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Dangerous Journey: 3 Places + 2 Escape + 2 Threats&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Monty Haul: 3 Objects + 2 Tools + 2 Foods&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Friendly Visit: 2 Friends + 3 Places + 2 Escapes&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Great Adventure: 1 of each Type&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Tricks of the Trade: 3 Tools + 4 Escapes&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Home and Hearth: 4 Objects + 3 Foods&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Full House: 4 Friends + 3 Objects&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    A Big Scary World: 4 Threats + 3 Places&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Weapons of Choice: 4 Tools + 3 Threats&amp;#10;-    You cannot make a meld of a type already made this game. &amp;#10;-    If you complete a meld discard your hand and draw 7 new cards. &amp;#10;-    If you don&amp;rsquo;t have a meld, you must discard your hand down to 6 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the first player to complete 3 melds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
